pyns -- Python port of the Neuroshare API
=========================================

Installation
------------

The pyns package and its installation depends on a few Python
modules.  These are: numpy, matplotlib, and psutil.  

On a Windows PC, these are easily installed using the Python 
distribution Python(x, y), which can be found at 
http://www.pythonxy.com

Further Information
-------------------

See the included documentation for more details as well as sort
examples.

The included directory pyns/examples has two short examples 
showing how to easily explore .nev and .nsx files using the
pyns package.